2. Part09: Added MapsStoneToNareBoundedModule (tex Lemma 1568)
   - Statement: For S : Stone and f : S → ℕ, ∃ N such that f(s) < N for all s
   - Proof strategy:
     a. For each n, fiber predicate d(n) = elemFromDecPred for (f(x) ≟ n)
     b. Spectrum of B/d is empty (every point is in some fiber)
     c. 0≡1 in B/d → extract-finJoin-bound gives ∃ N with finJoinBR d N ≡ 1
     d. Bound by contradiction: if f(s) ≥ N, all d(n) for n<N evaluate to false,
        so the join is false, contradicting finJoinBR d N ≡ 1
   - Helper lemmas:
     - Dec→Bool-yes, Dec→Bool-false: Dec→Bool characterization
     - boolhom-∨: BoolHom preserves ∨ (generalized from StoneSeparated)
     - joinAllFalse: if all components map to false, the join maps to false

